    {
        "sha": "4d61708ee5a406e7132b9dc0d12c729f546c6374",
        "author": "ADHITHYA SANKAR",
        "email": "adimuthanikatt@gmail.com",
        "date": "2025-12-22T14:38:42Z",
        "message": "fix: mark read all mails (#84)\n\n## Description\n\n<!-- What does this PR do? -->\nUse resultSizeEstimate to display number of unread emails which is\nfaster than getting all the emails.\nBut while actually marking it as read, paginate and get all emails and\nmark it as read\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [ ] I have tested my changes locally\n- [ ] Docker build works (if modified)\n\n## Related Issues\n\n<!-- Fixes #123 -->\n\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai\n-->\n- Schema: Allow MarkReadRequest.count = 0 (changed ge=1 → ge=0);\ndescription updated to \"Number of emails to mark. Use 0 to mark all.\"\n- Unread count optimization: get_unread_count() now uses the API's\nresultSizeEstimate (maxResults=1) to display a fast estimate instead of\nfetching all messages.\n- Mark-as-read behavior:\n  - mark_emails_as_read() now accepts count=0 to mark all unread emails.\n- Implements memory-efficient pagination (pages of up to 500), batching\nmark-as-read requests in chunks of 100.\n- Stops when requested count is reached or no more pages; trimming logic\nskipped when marking all.\n  - Improved input validation and clearer status/progress messages.\n- Frontend: GmailCleaner.MarkRead.start() sets count = 0 for the \"all\"\noption, removing DOM-based unread-count parsing.\n- Minor non-functional formatting tweaks in auth.py and download.py.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: adhi8580 <adhithya.sankar@rapyuta-robotics.com>",
